RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOLT FORTY FIVE sped to the lead at the start nd set the pace up the backstretch, took on the challenge of HUSKER BUTCH near the quarter pole, shook off rival leaving the turn, opened up to clear command and kept to task. HUSKER BUTCH tracked four deep in the flight sitting just off the early pacesetter, moved up to challenge eventual winner at the quarter pole, could not move on with rival turning for home but sustained a solid bid and finished clearly second best. RUDIANO raced off the compact second flight in the early stages, swung four wide into the lane, sustained a steady bid and secured a share. MR. MUNNINGS chased the leader between rivals in opening stages, ran on two wide around the turn then gave way in the lane. MEGA SHACK hustled along in pursuit along the rail in the early going, saved ground entering the lane then retreated in the lane. CAPTAIN DOZER chased three wide in early contention, flattened around the turn and continued to falter down the lane.

COLLECTED GLORY dueled inside a duo up the backstretch, continued to match strides with SWEET NELLIE into upper stretch, held a slight edge at the furlong marker, battled on gamely along the rail then got denied in final strides. PEACH STREET broke on top then settled back although never too far off the front runners, made a move three wide nearing the quarter pole, swung three to four wide into the lane, sustained a steady bid and finished well clear over the rest. SUGAR BELL raced just off the embattled trio in the opening quarter, hustled along two wide around the turn then tired in the drive. MIDNIGHTCANDYSTORM was not too far back in early stages, failed to advance under pressure along the rail around the turn then faded in the lane. LUV MAP dueled between rivals in opening stages, battled on past the three eighths pole then steadily retreated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 35000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $10,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING OR IOWA BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $30,000. Claiming Price $30,000 (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLAY'S MOON STONE tracked the pace two wide up the backstretch, crept closer around the far turn, given cue two wide at the head of the lane, dueled outside of ELUSIVE AMELIA, fought on gamely with rival holding a slight edge, battled on near equal terms approaching the wire and nailed foe in final stride. ELUSIVE AMELIA sped to the lead at the start and set the pace up the backstretch, remained the leader near the inside around the far turn, took on the challenge from CLAY'S MOON STONE at the head of the lane, battled back tenaciously from the inside, never gave up just got nipped on the wire. SWEET LAURA settled in the back and saved ground heading into the first turn, edged a bit closer and raced off the top trio, picked up the tempo midway around the far turn, hustled along three to four wide into the lane, sustained a steady bid and secured a share. ALL GOOD TIMES was the closet pursuer of the pacesetter up the backstretch, hustled along two wide around the far turn then flattened in the lane. MY DAMS ATITUDE settled off the early pace, swung three to four wide into the lane and had no response when called upon.

SWEETNESS TO dueled for the lead in opening strides racing outside of PAISELY'S VISION, battled on two wide around the turn, could not match strides in upper stretch but remained in range then flattened in late stages. WHISKEY WEDNESDAY rated off the pace in early stages, picked up the tempo past the half mile marker, gained closer contention along the rail around the far turn, briefly advanced to challenge the winner at the head of the lane, could not move on with rival, dueled for second place and nipped rival for the spot. MEGATAP dueled inside of MR.SOLO around the first turn and up the backstretch, got overtaken when the winner swept by midway around the far turn, still had kick left in reserve, ran on three wide down the lane and got nipped for place. HERZEN tracked the early pace, urged two wide around the far turn and failed to move on. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Bob Bryant S. PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 86. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS, FILLIES. (Iowa Registered and Foaled). Weight: 122 lbs. Non-winners of a sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs.; Non-winners of $24,000 allowed 4 lbs. (Maiden and claiming races not considered) Late nomination fee of $15,000 will be accepted at time of entry with $7,500 allocated to the purse and $7,500 to I.T.B.O.A. $300 to pass the entry box and $600 additional to start. $75,000 guaranteed which will first be reduced so as to allow $500 to be paid to each of the seventh through last place finishers with the remaining purse paid out as follows: 60% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 5% to fourth, 3% to fifth, 2% to sixth. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. Preference to start wi ll be given to those horses having accumulated the highest lifetime earnings at the closing time of entries. This preference will be utilized regardless of the ownership of the horses involved. Failure to draw into the race cancels all fees.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIT AND FAMOUS sped to the lead at the start and set the pace up the backstretch, held firm still unleashed around the turn, cut the corner entering the lane, given cue at the three sixteenths pole, responded willingly, widened to a commanding advantage and finished ridden out in the final sixteenth. MY HAPPINESS lacked early speed and raced three wide in the back, angled out wider and asked for more midway around the turn, swung five wide into the lane, responded in the lane, steadily gained ground and cleared second best. TARA'S TIME got pushed inward and came away last at the start, picked up the pace and raced four deep in the flight behind the leader late on the backstretch, hustled along four wide around the turn, sustained a mild bid down the lane and secured show. DIAL SUM IN was forwardly placed racing just off the early pacesetter, launched a two wide bid for the leader around teh turn, sustained bid to the furlong marker then gave way. SING LUCY SING raced in range up the backstretch, flattened around the turn and continued to falter in the lane. ESPIRIDION tracked the pacesetter, made a two wide move approaching the quarter pole then retreated in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN LUNA raced three wide in the second flight up the backstretch, loomed boldly three wide near the quarter pole, swung four wide into the lane, vied with MO CHOCTAW a furlong out then dug in gamely, seized command and kicked clear. IMPRESSOR raced two wide in the second flight up the backstretch, launched an outside bid heading into the lane, sustained a steady bid and just lasted for show.
